cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS

This paper is primarily focused on the problem of deciding the equivalence of SQL queries, which is a fundamental problem in data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also introduces a new formalism, U-semiring, which extends SQL's semiring semantics and can be implemented using proof assistants such as Coq for automated query reasoning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to categories such as cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of U-semiring by formally verifying query rewrite rules from both classical data management research papers and real-world SQL engines, which indicates that the paper may also be relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
